    <description>Ortep-3 for Windows is a MS-Windows version of the current release of [ORTEP-III (1.0.3)](http://web.ornl.gov/sci/ortep/ortep.html), which incorporates a Graphical User Interface (GUI) to make production of thermal ellipsoid plots much easier. 

#### License
WinGX is provided free of charge for academic, scientific, educational and non-commercial users, provided its use is acknowledged. A licence is required and [may be requested](http://www.chem.gla.ac.uk/~louis/software/licenseform.html).  If you do not yet have a license file, this package will still install, but WinGX will not start.

#### Package Parameters
The following package parameters can be set:

 * `/installDir:`_&lt;directory-path&gt;_
    
	The default location for WinGX is C:\wingx.  This package by default will install to a more standard, "%ProgramFiles(x86)%\WinGX", but the directory can be customized.
	
 * `/LicensePath:`_&lt;path-to-license-file&gt;_

    If you have a license file, "WinGX-License.txt", you can place it in "C:\Temp" (default) and this package will copy it to the proper location.  Adjust the location with this parameter.  The _path_ can be a file path or URL.

These parameters can be passed to the installer with the use of `-params`.
For example: 
	`-params '"/LicensePath:http://localsite.org/wingxlicense.txt"'`.

#### Features

WinGX uses SHELX format ASCII files, and contains the following [facilities and features](http://www.chem.gla.ac.uk/~louis/software/wingx/features.html).
